meanings.definition: António Ramalho Eanes (born 1935), a Portuguese general and politician who served as President of Portugal from 1976 to 1986.
meanings.english_definition: António Ramalho Eanes (born 1935), a Portuguese general and politician who served as President of Portugal from 1976 to 1986.

etymology.value: Derived from the given name João, meaning "John".
